        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adult patients who plan to undergo primary total knee arthroplasty on bilateral knee
             joint with a diagnosis of osteoarthritis or rheumatoid arthritis, etc.;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Those who do not meet the inclusion criteria;

          -  Neuromuscular dysfunction;

          -  Diseases affecting postoperative efficacy evaluation
